page.title: 10HOUSING
page.content: Many of the{farmhouses}are large brickbuilt dwellings dating from late 18th/ early 19th century. Others are black and white timber-framed houses dating from the 17th century and characteristic of Cheshire. The{villages}also have smaller dwellings, again some in brick and some in black and white timber. More{recent development}has taken place on the outskirts of villages, including council estates at Lostock Gralam and Wincham built in the 1950's, and private developments in the past 10 years. Near Pickmere Lake there are several wooden chalet-type houses, formerly{holiday homes,}some of which are now permanently occupied.
